# Class responsibilities (Responsibility Design)

Every **non-trivial type** must carry a class-level Javadoc block that states **what the type owns** in the collaboration — not a method-by-method recap.

Use this on **new types** and when **materially changing** an existing type's role. Update the block when collaborators or boundaries shift.

## When required

| Require block | Exempt (unless role is non-obvious) |
|---------------|-------------------------------------|
| Lifecycle managers, channels, transports, bridge/server/client facades | One-field records, trivial enums, generated code |
| Spring / Quarkus lifecycle beans | Lombok-style pure data DTOs with no behaviour |
| Test fixtures and infra (`*.tests.infra`) | Private nested types under ~15 lines with a single obvious job |
| SPI implementations, protocol/session handlers | |

When unsure, **document** — the block is cheap and prevents scope creep.

## Block template

Use HTML sections (matches existing test infra and Spring integration types):

```java
/**
 * <p>
 * <b>Responsibilities</b>
 * </p>
 * <ul>
 * <li><b>Knowing:</b> … state or facts this type is the source of truth for (optional).</li>
 * <li><b>Doing:</b> … actions it performs — lifecycle, I/O, mapping, orchestration (required).</li>
 * <li><b>Deciding:</b> … policy or branching only this type applies (optional).</li>
 * </ul>
 * <p>
 * <b>Collaborators:</b> {@link OtherType}, …
 * </p>
 * <p>
 * <b>Not responsible for:</b> … neighbouring concerns owned elsewhere.
 * </p>
 */
public final class Example { … }
```

### Section rules

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| **Knowing** | Invariants, cached handles, lifecycle flags, configuration snapshots this type holds. |
| **Doing** | Verbs: connect, close, route, map, subscribe, roll back — tie to domain terms from [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md). |
| **Deciding** | Optional — acceptance rules, retry policy, version negotiation when not obvious from names. |
| **Collaborators** | Types this class calls or is injected with; use `{@link …}` for project types. |
| **Not responsible for** | Prevents “god class” drift — name the **owner** of the excluded concern. |

Keep each bullet to **one line**. No tutorials; link ARCHITECTURE.md or user docs for long prose.

